<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-445-023  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 445 023.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  August 15 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Moscow: IBM revises hardware prices.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Tchashchin, Kirill.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   International Business Machines Corp. (prices).andO;Ticker:    IBM.andO;Topic:     Price CuttingSoviet UnionComputer industryMarketing StrategyPromotion of Product.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>MOSCOW: IBM REVISES HARDWARE PRICES MOSCOW, U.S.S.R., 1990 AUG 15 (NB) --IBM's Moscow office has issued a new price list featuring &quot;slightly lowered&quot;prices.andM;According to Berton Polischuk, head of representation, such price changes area regular process.andP;  &quot;We sometimes revise our prices here.andP;  It's a normalsituation,&quot; he told Newsbytes.andP;  He said that although prices for some itemshave &quot;slightly decreased,&quot; this doesn't represent any new trend in localmarketing.andM;Boris Soshnik, consultant for the MicroAge franchise in Moscow, toldNewsbytes that this price decrease could be the start of a new policy by IBMin the Soviet market.andP;  He said the prices now are almost the same as those inCentral Europe.andP;  &quot;IBM is starting a new, more active policy in the localmarket,&quot; he said.andP;  The IBM representative, however, didn't confirm thatopinion.andM;(Kirill Tchashchin/19900810/Press contact: Berton Polischuk, IBM Moscow, +7095 207-3119; Boris Soshnik, MicroAge Moscow, +7 095 229-7804)</TEXT></DOC>